Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.35,0:00:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's the way you suspect, Hotaro,\Nit would mean that at the very least,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.15,0:00:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,our Kanyasai came at the expense\Nof someone's high school life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.57,0:00:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.28,0:00:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At what?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.87,0:00:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the very fact that you even\Ntried to solve this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.41,0:00:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.29,0:00:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since we enrolled at Kami High,\Nyou've solved a number of mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.75,0:00:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the reason why you'd\Ngo to all that trouble, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.63,0:00:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's for Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.63,0:00:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Chitanda's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.68,0:00:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That works, too. But today was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.14,0:00:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could have bailed out on us, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.68,0:00:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The responsibility for unraveling that mystery\Ntoday was split between us four ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.06,0:00:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had said "I don't know" and taken off,\NI don't think anyone would have said a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.36,0:00:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That being said, why would you go so far as to lock\Nyourself in the bathroom to look for the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.82,0:00:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that for Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.99,0:01:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I've finally gotten\Ntired of being so gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.17,0:01:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As far as Chitanda goes, no one\Nis less energy efficient than she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.38,0:01:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being a club president,\Ncreating an anthology, taking tests,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.13,0:01:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and solving riddles from the past?\NI'm amazed she isn't exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.38,0:01:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and Ibara, too. It's highly\Nwasteful the way you do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.35,0:01:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that may be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.97,0:01:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand, the grass is\Nalways greener on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.52,0:01:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes when I watch you,\NI start to feel restless.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.52,0:01:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I want to be relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.28,0:01:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... even so, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.82,0:01:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't enjoy doing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.99,0:01:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I thought at least...\Nwell, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.04,0:01:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd try reasoning it out, and let myself\Nget involved, the way you guys do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.75,0:01:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.01,0:01:57.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.26,0:02:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, were you envious of our rosy lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.10,0:02:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.86,0:02:22.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.32,0:02:30.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away\Nthe awkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.67,0:02:38.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.55,0:02:43.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.97,0:02:49.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.35,0:02:54.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.86,0:02:59.95,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.32,0:03:06.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.74,0:03:14.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.21,0:03:19.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.80,0:03:25.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.06,0:03:33.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.48,0:03:46.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:51.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Truth About the\NHistoric Classic Lit Club
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.62,0:03:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rosy life, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.17,0:03:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what a rosy life is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.21,0:03:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.05,0:04:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, who's on a quest\Nthrough the past...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.01,0:04:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani Jun, who stood\Nup for the Kanyasai...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:06.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Classic Lit Club President Sekitani Jun
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what I want to become?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.64,0:04:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I really want a rosy life?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is a rosy life in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.27,0:04:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.36,0:04:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of rosy lives, there's Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.28,0:04:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm sure that ten years from now,\NI won't regret spending this time."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm 25, how will I look back\Non my life ten years before?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani Jun wouldn't have\Nhad any regrets. But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.59,0:04:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Oreki residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.39,0:04:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.14,0:04:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Sis? So you {\i1}are {\i0}alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How rude. You think I can't\Nsurvive a mugging or two?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.90,0:05:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}that's {\i0}the kind of trouble\Nyou got yourself into.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.32,0:05:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just reached Pristina yesterday.\NNo problems with my health or finances.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send you another letter\Nwhen I reach Sarajevo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.61,0:05:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I have to report.\NHow are things there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.62,0:05:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Oh, we're making\Nan anthology. {\i1}Hyouka{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yeah, {\i1}Hyouka{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.66,0:05:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're researching Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani Jun? There's a name\Nthat takes me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.09,0:05:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, his story is still going around.\NThen, is "Kanyasai" still off-limits?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.55,0:05:25.01,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Off-limits
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.01,0:05:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.05,0:05:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was such a tragedy, huh?\NIt sure put me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.80,0:05:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Off-limits? Tragedy? Put you off?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.43,0:05:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on here, this is\NSekitani Jun we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.93,0:05:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know. The\N"kindhearted hero," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure {\i1}you {\i0}know who you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.77,0:05:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, apparently, I {\i1}don't {\i0}know.\NSis, tell me about Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have enough time! Gotta go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.78,0:05:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D... D... Damn you, Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.08,0:05:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not done yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.08,0:06:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The theory I presented to\NChitanda and the others is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,either incorrect, or insufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:07.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that ten years from now,\NI won't regret spending this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.72,0:06:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he is still alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.68,0:06:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would Sekitani Jun have any regrets\Nabout his high school years?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think he'd have any reason to.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.81,0:06:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "hero,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.89,0:06:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who left high school as a martyr\Nfor his and his friends' passion,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.85,0:06:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would have no reason to\Nlament falling on his sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.02,0:06:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere along the line\NI convinced myself of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.65,0:06:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But is that really true?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.49,0:06:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be driven from school\Nover a mere culture festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.37,0:06:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and have a whole phase\Nof his life altered like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.33,0:06:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school life is all roses, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.83,0:06:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But is the intense rosiness of having that\Nhigh school life cut off midway through...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.92,0:06:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something you can still call rosy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.46,0:06:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgiving everything after you've\Nsacrificed yourself for your friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.26,0:06:54.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It was in no way a heroic tale
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.22,0:06:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't buy there being\Ntoo many heroes like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.89,0:06:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, Sis called it a "tragedy."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.85,0:06:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was Sekitani Jun's high school\Nlife really that rosy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.90,0:07:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to nail this down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.15,0:07:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Mayaka, did you get\Ncalled in by Hotaro, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.24,0:07:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm. He said to come to the club room after\Nschool, because he had something to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.25,0:07:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine, Hotaro taking the\Ntrouble to call anybody in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.08,0:07:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my memory, this is\Nan unprecedented event.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.59,0:07:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm busy with my Manga Club, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.30,0:07:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello. Thanks again for yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.18,0:07:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-mm, I had fun, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.72,0:07:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm more curious about where Hotaro is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.60,0:07:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.22,0:07:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like he's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.27,0:07:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.85,0:07:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you want to discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.35,0:07:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have something to add\Nto yesterday's matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.19,0:07:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think this will put it to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.36,0:07:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Listen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.82,0:07:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, it sounds as though
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.70,0:07:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's something more to this matter\Nthat I need to know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:08:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. We should be able to\Npretty well fill in the gaps today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.71,0:08:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.58,0:08:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, Oreki? Fill in what gaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.38,0:08:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By gaps, I mean gaps. I'm working\Nto amend something that is incomplete
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.01,0:08:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it more complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.51,0:08:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incomplete? Hotaro, are you saying\Nyour theory was incomplete?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.10,0:08:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. It might be off\Nin the wrong direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.18,0:08:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or it might not have gone far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.06,0:08:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know? And yet\Nyou still called us all in?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.31,0:08:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable.\NJust listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.36,0:08:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should have given\Nmore weight to {\i1}Hyouka{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.40,0:08:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It clearly states in the foreword\Nthat Sekitani Jun's story
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.57,0:08:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is in no way a heroic tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.41,0:08:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We read that yesterday\Nand excluded it, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.78,0:08:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We said that ultimately, that was\Nthe writer's own mental image.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.79,0:08:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But it's also possible\Nthat we were misled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.25,0:08:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, when you start saying that...\NAlso,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.46,0:08:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's this passage about "the conflicts,\Nthe sacrifices, and even his smile."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.30,0:08:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we sure "sacrifices"\Nhere really means "sacrifices"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.30,0:08:54.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Sacrifices
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.34,0:08:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can also be read as "offering," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.13,0:08:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is spelled differently, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.84,0:08:58.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Offering
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.84,0:08:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It starts with the character for "alive."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.76,0:09:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you can write it as "sacrifice"\Nbut read it as "offering."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.56,0:09:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Originally, the two meant the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to our academic\Nall-star to bottom-line it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.06,0:09:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, so we get that there's\Na different way to read it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.57,0:09:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but unless you're the person who wrote it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.65,0:09:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's no way to tell which way\Nis the right way, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.57,0:09:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed there is. We could always ask them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.16,0:09:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.58,0:09:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who wrote the\Nforeword... Koriyama Yoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.29,0:09:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,45 years ago, she was a\N1st-year in high school,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.33,0:09:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and today, she'd be 60 or 61.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.46,0:09:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You searched for this woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.63,0:09:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have to. She's right nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, miss library assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.35,0:09:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Is that right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.22,0:09:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.93,0:09:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.68,0:09:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, she's right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.68,0:09:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our librarian, Itoigawa-{\i1}sensei{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.44,0:09:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Itoigawa Yoko-{\i1}sensei{\i0}... her\Nmaiden name is Koriyama, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.02,0:09:51.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Itoigawa Yoko
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.65,0:09:54.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Koriyama Yoko\NItoigawa Yoko
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.28,0:09:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. The "Yo" that spells "Yoko"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.78,0:09:56.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:09:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,isn't a common one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.66,0:10:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention that Itoigawa-{\i1}sensei\N{\i0}is just the right age.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Add to that the way she reacted when she\Nfound out that we were the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really {\i1}are {\i0}weird, Oreki.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.38,0:10:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I've been next\Nto her this whole time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't notice that when\NI heard the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.88,0:10:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you don't want to let Chi-{\i1}chan\N{\i0}peek around inside your head?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.97,0:10:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said before, I just luck\Ninto these flashes of brilliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I don't need\NChitanda dissecting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.22,0:10:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then, if we ask Itoigawa-{\i1}sensei\N{\i0}about all of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.10,0:10:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll find out what\Nhappened 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.65,0:10:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why it wasn't a heroic tale,\Nwhy the cover picture is what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why it has the odd-sounding\Ntitle of {\i1}Hyouka{\i0}, as well as...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.66,0:10:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what happened to your uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.24,0:10:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But do you have any proof\Nthat it really is Itoigawa-{\i1}sensei{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't born yesterday. In fact,\NI've already confirmed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From her, directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.46,0:10:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. She said that when she was\Na 2nd-year, she was the club president.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.30,0:10:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also set up an appointment\Nto talk to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.47,0:11:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, it's almost time.\NLet's go to the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.02,0:11:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}are {\i0}awfully fired up, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.94,0:11:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.11,0:11:18.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Geshi{\i0} ('Height of Summer')\NWhen the sun\Nwaxeth hottest, and the day is at its longest
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.15,0:11:18.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.99,0:11:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Itoigawa-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.58,0:11:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.88,0:11:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I still have\Na little work left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be okay if we spoke out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.26,0:11:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Ibara-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand you have\Nsomething you'd like to ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Before we do, though, I'd like to confirm\Nsomething once again, in front of the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Itoigawa-{\i1}sensei{\i0}, your maiden\Nname is Koriyama, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.61,0:11:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.48,0:12:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you are the one\Nwho wrote this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am. Though I'm surprised\Nthat this is still around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.83,0:12:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a fair idea of what\Nyou'd like to ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.79,0:12:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd like to know more about that\Nmovement that took place 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.01,0:12:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo. She does know, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.68,0:12:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would you ask now about\Nsomething that happened so long ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.76,0:12:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought everyone had\Nforgotten it by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.39,0:12:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, if Chitanda here wasn't such a wild curiosity\Nmonkey, taking an interest in every little thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.23,0:12:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we probably never\Nwould have come upon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.36,0:12:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wild curiosity monkey?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.36,0:12:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg your pardon. I meant junkie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.99,0:12:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, my! I mean, a\Njunkie, of all things...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why are you so interested\Nin that movement?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.62,0:12:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Sekitani Jun...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.66,0:12:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is my uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.63,0:12:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that right? Sekitani Jun-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.96,0:13:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That name brings back memories.\NIs he doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.38,0:13:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not know. He has\Ngone missing in India.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.35,0:13:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really? I've always wanted\Nto see him once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.02,0:13:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see him once again, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.28,0:13:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Itoigawa-{\i1}sensei{\i0}, please tell us,\Nwhat happened 45 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.61,0:13:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why was the incident involving\Nmy uncle "not a hero's tale"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.95,0:13:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the Classic Lit Club's\Nanthology named {\i1}Hyouka{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.00,0:13:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much of Oreki-{\i1}san'{\i0}s\Nsupposition is correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.04,0:13:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s supposition?\NWhat would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.63,0:13:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.09,0:13:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki took some fragmentary\Ninformation and tied it together,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,inferring what took place 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.22,0:13:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please have a listen to what he has to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.51,0:13:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, well, why don't you tell\Nme all about it in my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.77,0:13:56.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Librarian's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.10,0:14:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. And that's why you\Nassume that his expulsion
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.73,0:14:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was put off until October?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.49,0:14:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That is the extent of my conjecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.74,0:14:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You put together this story from\Nonly the material you have here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just brought together\Neveryone else's reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.12,0:14:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm astounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.34,0:14:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I way off base?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.17,0:14:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's like you witnessed it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.76,0:14:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}kun{\i0}, what you say\Nis almost entirely true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.84,0:14:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What more would you like to ask me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.39,0:14:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Hotaro says that there is\Nsomething about it that's incomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.06,0:14:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is one thing that\NI would like to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.31,0:14:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Sekitani Jun willingly take the hit\Nfor all the other students?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.03,0:14:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he act on behalf of the student body,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.78,0:14:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,heroically holding his head high,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.70,0:14:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and forfeit his rosy high school\Nlife to leave the school?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.71,0:15:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really do see right\Nthrough things, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.38,0:15:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... This was such a long time ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.30,0:15:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I still remember it quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.88,0:15:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, Kamiyama\NHigh School's culture festival
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.35,0:15:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was almost like the whole\Npurpose in life for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.02,0:15:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might say that the energy that\Nwas surging throughout Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.60,0:15:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had taken on the form of\NKami High's culture festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.82,0:15:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the year that I enrolled,\Nthe movement went too far,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.07,0:15:33.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and came this close to\Nbecoming a full-blown riot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.37,0:15:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That year, the principal\Napparently dropped a bombshell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.16,0:15:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"We can't content ourselves with being a\Nsmall-time school in a sleepy little town."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.62,0:15:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone thought that he meant\Nthe culture festival was abolished.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.38,0:15:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He unilaterally gave notice\Nthat the culture festival schedule
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.13,0:15:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was being shortened from\Nthe usual five days to two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.26,0:15:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That acted as the trigger\Nthat set off a huge uproar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.05,0:16:04.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Rally
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.18,0:15:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole school was on edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.39,0:15:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were banners, and\Npublic speeches, and then,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.10,0:16:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the movement got to the point where\Nthey tried to assert their collective will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They must have been pretty serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it was a world that we\Ncouldn't even imagine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.37,0:16:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't as glorious as all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.45,0:16:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, we were acting like\Nour toys had been taken from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.29,0:16:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we were throwing a\Ntantrum because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.41,0:16:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.83,0:16:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, looking back on it now,\NI think I can say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.13,0:16:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, a countermovement against shortening\Nthe culture festival was organized.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.84,0:16:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody came forward to be the leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.89,0:16:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were afraid of being punished,\Nas pathetic as that sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.48,0:16:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who ended up\Ndrawing the short straw
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.73,0:16:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}'s uncle, Sekitani Jun-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.90,0:16:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was someone else who\Nactually ran the show,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.36,0:16:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but that person never made his name public.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.36,0:16:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, the plan to shorten\Nthe culture festival fell through,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.24,0:17:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but eagerly worked up and whipped\Ninto a frenzy by our protest movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.62,0:17:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we went too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.08,0:17:09.71,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Teachers accept our demands!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.21,0:17:08.13,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,On strike! Right is on our side!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.71,0:17:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As part of our movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.13,0:17:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the students were boycotting classes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.01,0:17:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when it had reached\Na full head of steam,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.09,0:17:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we boosted morale with a bonfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.85,0:17:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the night the incident happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.64,0:17:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fire broke out in the\Ncombat sports building.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.06,0:17:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The building was partially\Ndestroyed under the fire hoses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.44,0:17:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was something that\Nthe school could not excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.73,0:17:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The school didn't have\Nthe police intervene,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.07,0:17:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but later, when the incident\Nwas called into question,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.57,0:17:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there wasn't a single student\Nwho could rebut them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.16,0:17:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, the school decided to make an\Nexample of the nominal leader of the movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.00,0:17:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani-{\i1}san{\i0}, by expelling him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.29,0:17:50.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Expulsion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.76,0:17:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We, the students, could not do anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.72,0:17:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and just watched on as it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.22,0:18:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonetheless, Sekitani-{\i1}san\N{\i0}remained quiet, right up to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.19,0:18:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You asked if Sekitani-{\i1}san{\i0} came forward by choice\Nas a martyr for the other students, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.15,0:18:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know the answer to that now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.66,0:18:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Several years passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.37,0:18:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and bit by bit, the culture\Nfestival was shortened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.37,0:18:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It now runs for three days, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.67,0:18:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the end of the story. Is there\Nanything else you'd like to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.30,0:18:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, the cover of the anthology\Ndepicts what happened back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.68,0:18:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The dog is the school,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the rabbits are the students,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.06,0:18:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the rabbit that is taking the dog\Ndown with him is Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.81,0:18:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the reason why the combat sports building\Nis by far the oldest facility at Kami High
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.36,0:18:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because it was rebuilt at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.44,0:18:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. 20 years ago,\Nwhen the school buildings were rebuilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.28,0:19:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the combat sports building\Nwas not yet that old,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.37,0:19:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it was left as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.83,0:19:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you don't use the term "Kanyasai," do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.83,0:19:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By any chance, does the\N"Kanya" in "Kanyasai"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.42,0:19:13.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyama
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.09,0:19:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stand not for\N"Kamiyama," but for "Sekitani"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.79,0:19:16.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani ('Kanya')
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.88,0:19:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.93,0:19:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The origin of the term "Kanyasai."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.18,0:19:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To honor their hero, they took "Sekitani-{\i1}sai{\i0}"\Nand switched the reading to make it "Kanyasai."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.64,0:19:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.77,0:19:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But calling it that is misleading.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.56,0:19:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani Jun didn't become\Na hero because he wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If people knew that, they wouldn't\Nuse the term "Kanyasai," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.32,0:19:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.61,0:19:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That name was banned\Nwithin the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.87,0:19:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, do you know why my uncle\Ngave the name {\i1}Hyouka{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.79,0:19:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the Classic Lit Club's anthology?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.05,0:20:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Sekitani-{\i1}san{\i0}, sensing that\Nhe was going to be expelled,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.18,0:20:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was uncharacteristically insistent\Non selecting that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.51,0:20:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said it was the most that he could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.48,0:20:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.10,0:20:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the meaning behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.73,0:20:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.90,0:20:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really not know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.19,0:20:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that\Nnobody ever interpreted it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.03,0:20:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That... ridiculous message?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.12,0:20:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.78,0:20:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know? What we just\Nheard should make it clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.75,0:20:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hyouka {\i0}is just some silly wordplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.62,0:20:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wordplay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.79,0:20:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani Jun made sure to express\Nhow he felt to the Classic Lit Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.34,0:20:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all the way down to its\Nsuccessors, including us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.88,0:20:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He put it right in the anthology's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.68,0:20:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean? Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},\Ndo you know what {\i1}Hyouka {\i0}means?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.18,0:20:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.81,0:20:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.52,0:20:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.40,0:20:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you get if you translate\N{\i1}Hyouka {\i0}into English?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.44,0:21:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ice cream," you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.86,0:21:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ice cream... That's what the message is?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.74,0:21:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, it's wordplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.63,0:21:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.55,0:21:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.72,0:21:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real statement that\NSekitani Jun was making is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.75,0:21:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.00,0:22:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked my uncle what {\i1}Hyouka {\i0}meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.80,0:22:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I did, he said to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.05,0:22:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he told me to be strong.\NThat someday, if I was ever weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.18,0:22:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If ever... Yes, if the day ever came\Nwhen I couldn't even scream...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.73,0:22:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that ever happened,\NI would be eaten alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.46,0:22:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so scared of being\Neaten alive that I started crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.93,0:22:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness. I remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.18,0:22:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I can let my uncle go for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.69,0:22:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All thanks to you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.27,0:23:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.86,0:23:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, I just chanced upon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.95,0:23:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. You chanced upon it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.87,0:23:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ice cream."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.54,0:23:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I scream."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.88,0:23:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I drew up a rough draft\Nand schedule for the anthology.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.01,0:23:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how you make a rough draft, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.39,0:23:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is amazing, Mayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.39,0:23:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It is?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.64,0:23:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But where did you learn\Nhow to do something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.52,0:23:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't really matter, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.31,0:23:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.40,0:23:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about this "The Case of\Nthe Kindhearted Hero:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.82,0:23:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Truth That Was Hidden\NFor 45 Years" special feature...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.95,0:23:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.03,0:23:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I in charge of writing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.74,0:23:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're {\i0}the one who solved the mystery,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.24,0:23:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it's only fair that {\i1}you {\i0}write it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.00,0:24:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It runs for the most pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.00,0:24:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well of course it does.\NAfter all, it is our featured article.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.75,0:24:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.09,0:24:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's too hard for you,\NI can try to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.80,0:24:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that sounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.88,0:24:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}! This is about the only\Ntime that he's good for anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.14,0:24:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, we have to work him hard, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.68,0:24:21.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.23,0:24:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No complaining, Oreki, just\Nstart thinking of an outline!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.19,0:24:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}, about the\Ncolumn you'll be in charge of...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.94,0:24:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, it's surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.61,0:24:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.57,0:24:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The anthology article.\NYou ended up accepting it after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.66,0:24:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say I accepted it\Nso much as I couldn't get out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.33,0:24:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, I guess it might count\Nas a tribute to Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.84,0:24:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of things that are surprising...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.01,0:24:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.96,0:24:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier, I suggested that you ask\Nfor Satoshi and Ibara's help, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.22,0:24:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were reluctant at first,\Nso why did you suddenly decide to?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.06,0:25:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.85,0:25:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, you said that if I\Ndidn't solve my uncle's mystery,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.61,0:25:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,someday, the statute of\Nlimitations might run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.82,0:25:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that ten years\Nfrom now, I might not care,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.99,0:25:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the feelings that I'm having now...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.41,0:25:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're something that\NI don't want to think...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.66,0:25:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will mean nothing in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.04,0:25:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it's the present\Nthat I'm living in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.34,0:25:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.84,0:25:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.26,0:25:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still not sure I understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.22,0:25:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.68,0:25:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.40,0:25:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, anyhow, good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.15,0:25:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.49,0:25:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dear Oreki Tomoe-{\i1}dono{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.41,0:26:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending this letter to ask a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.49,0:26:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much did you know\Nabout the Classic Lit Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.21,0:26:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was your intention in making\Nme join the Classic Lit Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.38,0:26:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know the style of person I am.\NRight, an energy conservationist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.47,0:26:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't joined the Classic Lit Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.09,0:26:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never would have even\Nreconsidered my style.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.55,0:26:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you anticipate that, by me\Njoining the Classic Lit Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.56,0:26:25.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would be shaken up the way I was?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.19,0:26:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And as for {\i1}Hyouka{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.69,0:26:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I know about the Sekitani Jun\Nincident through the anthologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.78,0:26:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come to think that this\Nstyle of mine isn't so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.07,0:26:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, relatively speaking, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.12,0:26:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then, Sis, that would\Nalmost make you...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.96,0:26:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.71,0:26:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider everything I've written\Nhere to be an update from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.80,0:26:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a nice trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.68,0:27:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the advice.... Oreki Hotaro."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.02,0:27:08.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.02,0:27:11.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.77,0:27:15.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.78,0:27:21.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.25,0:27:41.30,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.10,0:27:52.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.52,0:27:59.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.03,0:28:04.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.37,0:28:10.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.12,0:28:15.13,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.13,0:28:18.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.17,0:28:21.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.88,0:28:25.85,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.85,0:28:31.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.19,0:28:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Committing a Cardinal Sin."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.19,0:28:43.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Committing a Cardinal Sin
